properties.name: Dialogue
properties.value: Unfortunately I can't let you through.  There was a mutant spotted in the Galviston woods.  Reports say it has been eating low level morphs.  Run along now and play.

properties.value:
What do you mean where are you?
You are in Coda, a wildlife preserve that is home to some diverse genetic species on the planet!

properties.name: dialogue
properties.value:
Sorry, the Galviston Woods are closed temporarily. 
A violent morph was spotted. 
Don't worry! The Police are tracking it.
You can go through when it is safe again.

properties.name: dialogue
properties.value: Maria is not home today, she may have gone out into Galviston Woods, but I hear there was a morph around.  I hope she is ok.

properties.name: Dialogue
properties.value:
They say those who drink nuclear morph can become corrupt and turn bad.  
I wonder what it does to animals?

properties.name: dialogue
properties.value:
Did you know that there are two kinds of morph power?
Do you want me to tell you about them?
[yes_no]
[yes: Star power is the power of space.  It was founded by an alien race thousands of years ago. Stardust morphology turns your genome into one of an extraterrestrial.
Then there's nuke morphs.  They come from radioactive metals deep in the planet.  The metalic power binds with morphagen DNA and makes the corrupt into walking bombs!
Cool huh?
I'm a nut about morphology, if you can't tell. 
 Thanks for listening to me.  Here, take this.  I found it on the ground by Maria's house:
[get_item:lunchbox]
]

With all the talk about the rogue morph in the woods, it's nice to find a quiet place to read before taking a nap.
Yeah, well that's how introverts are. [Emoticon_Smiley]
